      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm working on this embedded c++ project for an automotive sensor module and we're seeing a slow memory leak in the telemetry loop. it takes about 4-6 hours of operation before the heap is totally exhausted. i think it might be in the buffer allocation logic. can u look at this snippet and tell me how i should go about finding the exact leak?\n\n```cpp\nvoid process_sensor_data(SensorData* data) {\n    if (data != nullptr) {\n        TelemetryPacket* packet = new TelemetryPacket();\n        packet->timestamp = data->timestamp;\n        packet->payload = new uint8_t[data->size];\n        memcpy(packet->payload, data->raw_bytes, data->size);\n        \n        // push to queue for transmission\n        transmit_queue.push(packet);\n    }\n}\n```\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
